procstep.procdesc: The following steps were performed by ESRI: Extracted eur_p.shp from AND Global Road Data. Copied all boundary features inside water bodies from Europe Major Water. Removed water body features. Added missing boundary between Armenia and Iran from Europe Major Water and coded it from ESRI Data & Maps 2002 Europe Countries. Added Malta and coded it using eur_l.shp from AND Global Road Data. Corrected the projections for several islands with data from World Vector Shoreline. Changed Yugoslavia to Serbia and Montenegro. Combined nation and province codes as the common attribute and joined each of the three provincial lookup tables to the data set. Aggregated Luxembourg and Denmark second order divisions to create first order divisions by matching the higher order divisions in ESRI Data & Maps 2002 World Administrative Units 2002. Repeated the process for Poland and Estonia using online sources of @Poland and Statistical Office of Estonia. Added three attributes, PROV1, PROV2, and PROV3, and coded them by combining province and country names. Corrected coding errors. Summarized on each attribute, PROV1, PROV2, and PROV3, and merged features to create each of the three province-level shapefiles. For each of the three new shapefiles, added and coded attributes SQKM and COLORMAP and rearranged and renamed the remaining attributes. Created ArcView legend files (.avl), ArcGIS™ layer files (.lyr), projection files (.prj), and spatial indices.
